<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mi> 1f </m:mi>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
 and 
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mi> 2f </m:mi>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
 after collision. For the collision, it is imperative that velocity of the projectile (
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mi> 1i </m:mi>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
) is greater than that of target (
<m:math>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> v </m:mi>
<m:mi> 2i </m:mi>
</m:msub>
</m:math>
). Now the momentum equations is :
</para>
